main.title: Quick Start Guide
main.subtitle: A step-by-step guide to building your first Dullahan site.
main.content:
Overview

Much of the documentation is intended to be used as a reference sheet for various features, explaining how they work and what options and settings they provide.

What we're building

You might have known it was coming next â€“ it's the staple of every CMS walkthrough. How easy is it to build a blog? You're about to find out.

But first, let's talk about what a blog is. A "blog" is a collection of posts that shares common traits or attributes. A typical blog post might contain a title, featured image, an author, a few tags, and the article content.

Let's detail exactly what we're going to build, and then build it.

Here's our todo list:

  • Create a blog "Collection" with the following fields: title, excerpt, and content
  • Create a blog detail page

Create a new Collection

Head back to the Control Panel and click on the Collections link in the sidebar. Click the blue Create Collection button and then call your new collection "Blogs".

Edit collection template

Click Templates link in the sidebar and click "Blogs" inside templates list view. Here you can see default collection template.

We said that we want our collection to have next fields: title, excerpt, and content

We already have title but we want to add excerpt and content to the blogs collection. Let's do that now! Click on the create field button.

Next we need to choose right module for our template. I would say that for excerpt textarea is quite fiting. Let's click on Textarea module.

Let's fill out display, instructions & finally let's say that this module is required, than click next.

We can reapeat the same proccess, but now for the content field. We probably want for the content to have more freedom, so in this case I would choose Rich Text Editor as a fitting module type for our field. Let's give it display a value: Content & set it to be required.

Now we're essentially done with customizing our blog template & we should have something like this.

Create collection entry

Let's navigate to Collections -> Blogs -> Click on button "Create collections entry"

Now we can see our creation come to life. Let's add some content & create our first entry.

Gotta fetch'em all

Let's fetch our blogs via REST API.

/api/collections/blogs & we should get back all available blogs.
